description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

```java
package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
```

2. Compile using the following command: `ajc -d subpackage subpackage\Test.java`

Observed Behavior: A directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

Expected Behavior: The compiled class file is placed in the existing "subpackage" directory without creating a subdirectory.

Note: This issue does not occur when using `javac subpackage\Test.java`.

